RACE.RACE_TEXT: GULFSTREAM PARK RACE 1 5F Turf CR: 68. Maiden Optional Claiming Purse 40000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD FLORIDA-BRED, OR MAIDEN CLAIMING PRICE $50,000. Weight, 118 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000. (If deemed inadvisable to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the Tapeta Course at Five Furlongs) (Rail at 28 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: STARSHIP SUNRISE tracked in the three path, was driven around the two path rounding the turn, swung out to the five path into the lane, rallied outside of foes and was up in the closing stages. BEAUTY OF THE SEA prompted the pace in the four path, ranged up and was cued right handed rounding the turn, remained in the four path entering the stretch, ran on to take the lead just past the eighth pole, but was overtaken by the outer eventual winner late to finish with place. ROYAL BLOOD brushed with an inner foe at the start and raced off the pace in the two path, was coaxed along the inside midway around the turn, tipped out to the three path at the top of the lane, drifted out under left handed urging thru the lane, and finished evenly for show. OLYMPIC ARTIST pressed in the three path, was under rousing between foes rounding the turn, but faded from the three path in the stretch. MOONLIGHT VISION rated in the five path, was ridden in the six path entering the stretch, but was no factor. MINXY set the pace in the two path, received right handed cues into the lane, but yielded in the final furlong. DAN'S CANDI GIRL stalked in the three path, tipped inside early around the turn and remained inside of rivals into the stretch, but was blocked thru the stretch and unable to threaten. GREEK MOJO brushed with an outer foe at the start, chased in the four path early but never menaced. NO CHANGES WERE MADE AFTER AN INQUIRY WAS HELD TO LOOK AT THE STRETCH RUNS OF DAN'S CANDI GIRL AND MINXY.
